            <!-- ============================================================ -->
            <!-- Measure 8 (final): "^Bb"D3/2 "^G#"F/2 "^Eb"E -->
            <!-- Bb(V), G#=Ab(IV), Eb(I) — final authentic cadence -->
            <!-- Melody: D4(=Bb3 actually... wait: B=Bb, D=Db, E=Eb in Eb key) -->
            <!-- ABC: D=Db4 (key Eb = D has accid flat), F=F4(??) -->
            <!-- Wait — in K:Eb, D natural = Db, but "D" is a white key letter. -->
            <!-- Actually in ABC K:Eb: Bb, Eb, Ab are applied to b, e, a. -->
            <!-- D is not in the key signature, so D = D natural -->
            <!-- "^Bb" annotation: Bb=V, melody D=D4 (Db... hmm) -->
            <!-- Let me re-read: "^Bb"D3/2 "^G#"F/2 "^Eb"E -->
            <!-- D in ABC K:Eb = D natural (not flat), F = F natural, E = Eb4 -->
            <!-- Bb chord: V, melody D4 = 3rd of Bb chord. OK. -->
            <!-- G#=Ab chord: IV, F4 = accidental? No, F is diatonic. Ab chord with F = 6th -->
            <!-- Eb(I): E=Eb4 (key sig) -->
            <!-- Melody: D=D4 dotted quarter, F=F4 eighth, E=Eb4 -->
            <!-- Rhythm: D3/2 = dotted quarter, F/2 = eighth, E = 2 beats? -->
            <!-- Total: 1.5 + 0.5 + ? The original said D3/2 F/2 E with meter 4/4 -->
            <!-- So D3/2=1.5 beats, F/2=0.5 beats, E= 2 beats = whole measure 4 beats OK -->
            <!-- ============================================================ -->
